"used to generate the default :file:`records.config`. Just add the "
"variable to the file in an appropriate place with a proper default as "
"this will now override whatever default you put in the code for new "
"installs."
msgstr ""

# 9249c29196f149d58eee367f310c8fa1
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:237
msgid "Handling Updates"
msgstr ""

# 050e1459558740e48cf4d7fd89ee4895
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:239
msgid ""
"The simplest mechanism for handling updates is the "
"``REC_EstablishStaticConfigXXX`` family of functions. This mechanism will"
" cause the value in the indicated instance to be updated in place when an"
" update to :file:`records.config` occurs. This is done asynchronously "
"using atomic operations. Use of these variables must keep that in mind."
msgstr ""

# 3e2ab6adb7b14e35a174e08ee06e90e5
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:245
msgid ""
"If a variable requires additional handling when updated a callback can be"
" registered which is called when the variable is updated. This is what "
"the ``REC_EstablishStaticConfigXXX`` calls do internally with a callback "
"that simply reads the new value and writes it to storage indicated by the"
" call parameters. The functions used are the ``link_XXX`` static "
"functions in |RecCore.cc|_."
msgstr ""

# a741aece415e4dafb1b992f6702866a2
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:251
msgid ""
"To register a configuration variable callback, call "
"``RecRegisterConfigUpdateCb`` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

# f8b11f923266463d9ef530ded4291eb3
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:255
msgid "``char const*`` *name*"
msgstr ""

# e9de92af32ce4fbbb25aa8be45d13f9a
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:255
msgid "The variable name."
msgstr ""

# 6364c8e08d434302b0eb3c715e274985
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:262
msgid "*callback*"
msgstr ""

# 83958090c0604b6a9f83c40fbc52f25f
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:258
msgid ""
"A function with the signature ``<int (char const* name, RecDataT type, "
"RecData data, void* cookie)>``. The :arg:`name` value passed is the same "
"as the :arg:`name` passed to the registration function as is the "
":arg:`cookie` argument. The :arg:`type` and :arg:`data` are the new value"
" for the variable. The return value is currently ignored. For future "
"compatibility return ``REC_ERR_OKAY``."
msgstr ""

# b7c4038aa72e45519037f0a9eaea7817
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:266
msgid "``void*`` *cookie*"
msgstr ""

# ed491646e1d745baa2f5d8f38c5df565
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:265
msgid ""
"A value passed to the *callback*. This is only for the callback, the "
"internals simply store it and pass it on."
msgstr ""

# cfa2ba6b53734abfb4c018b3f3f5a5b4
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:268
msgid ""
"*callback* is called under lock so it should be quick and not block. If "
"that is necessary a :term:`continuation` should be scheduled to handle "
"the required action."
msgstr ""

# 9184ba4ae7644132bca862d6fcad2494
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:274
msgid ""
"The callback occurs asynchronously. For HTTP variables as described in "
"the next section, this is handled by the more specialized HTTP update "
"mechanisms. Otherwise it is the implementor's responsibility to avoid "
"race conditions."
msgstr ""

# 591d812a69604bb89e1f32e9511ee52f
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:281
msgid "HTTP Configuation Values"
msgstr ""

# e19568b6cd4b402ab4d17df7e4244f2a
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:283
msgid ""
"Variables used for HTTP processing should be declared as members of the "
"``HTTPConfigParams`` structure (but see :ref:`overridable-config-vars` "
"for further details) and use the specialized HTTP update mechanisms which"
" handle synchronization and initialization issues."
msgstr ""

# 755e5e9480fa46c6819eb7067f29fe3a
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:288
msgid ""
"The configuration logic maintains two copies of the ``HTTPConfigParams`` "
"structure, the master copy and the current copy. The master copy is kept "
"in the ``m_master`` member of the ``HttpConfig`` singleton. The current "
"copy is kept in the ConfigProcessor. The goal is to provide a (somewhat) "
"atomic update for configuration variables which are loaded individually "
"in to the master copy as updates are received and then bulk copied to a "
"new instance which is then swapped in as the current copy. The HTTP state"
" machine interacts with this mechanism to avoid race conditions."
msgstr ""

# f5eb20271c9344798db5f4cf8bd30d59
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:297
msgid ""
"For each variable, a mapping between the variable name and the "
"appropriate member in the master copy should be established between in "
"the ``HTTPConfig::startup`` method. The ``HttpEstablishStaticConfigXXX`` "
"functions should be used unless there is a strong, explicit reason to not"
" do so."
msgstr ""

# e95388113971429896e3108f80bcc169
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:302
msgid ""
"The ``HTTPConfig::reconfigure`` method handles the current copy of the "
"HTTP configuration variables. Logic should be added here to copy the "
"value from the master copy to the current copy. Generally this will be a "
"simple assignment. If there are dependencies between variables, those "
"should be checked and enforced in this method."
msgstr ""

# adbe59db7ab94f898733844a0a53e48a
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:311
msgid "Overridable Variables"
msgstr ""

# 3c937aaaced54a309bd5ab34dcbf1da3
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:313
msgid ""
"HTTP related variables that are changeable per transaction are stored in "
"the ``OverridableHttpConfigParams`` structure, an instance of which is "
"the ``oride`` member of ``HTTPConfigParams`` and therefore the points in "
"the previous section still apply. The only difference for that is the "
"further ``.oride`` member specifier in the structure references."
msgstr ""

# f8cb71d1f716492998bca7b9af997522
#: ../../developer-guide/config-vars.en.rst:318
msgid ""
"The variable is required to be accessible from the transaction API. In "
"addition to any custom API functions used to access the value, the "
"following items are required for generic access:"
msgstr ""

